    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-04-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-04-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="399"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d399">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Muruaga</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-04-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 3, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 13.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 20th ultimo, addressed to Mr. Uhl as Acting Secretary,
                    communicating copy of a telegram from the Governor-General of Cuba in regard to
                    an alleged statement of “sailors” touching an entry in the log book of the <hi
                        rend="italic">Conde Venadito</hi>, relative to firing upon a vessel said to
                    have shown the British flag off Cape Maysi on the 8th instant, which vessel the
                    Governor-General supposes to have been the <hi rend="italic">Alliança</hi>.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
